Multiple Variables

Which artist appeared most

hot100 |&gt;
  filter(rank == 1, date &gt; "2015-01-01") |&gt;
  distinct(artist, song) |&gt;
  group_by(artist) |&gt;
  summarise(n = n()) |&gt;
  arrange(-n) |&gt;
  head(10) |&gt;
  ggplot(aes(x = artist, y = n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip()










Which song (song & artist) has been on the charts the most?

hot100 |&gt;
  group_by(song, artist) |&gt;
  summarize(appearance = n()) |&gt;
  arrange(-appearance) |&gt;
  head(10)

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'song'. You can override using the
`.groups` argument.









